M||tags|[fi, pl, runway, cac, ltv, mrr, margin, roi]
M||inte|Master rv and retention metrics to understand SaaS business momentum, evaluate pd-mk fit, and make data-driven decisions abt growth investments. Use this to calculate key metrics, interpret tn, identify problems early, and communicate business health to stakeholders.
M||tp|cp
M||them|fi-metrics
M||best|
M||scen|
M||esti|"10-15 min"
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Master rv and retention metrics to understand SaaS business momentum, evaluate pd-mk fit, and make data-driven decisions abt growth investments. Use this to calculate key metrics, interpret tn, identify problems early, and communicate business health to stakeholders.
M|Purp|tx|This is not a business intelligence tool—it's a framework for PMs to understand which metrics matter, how to calculate them correctly, and what actions to take based on the numbers.
M|Reve|tx|The "top-line" metrics that measure how much money the business generates.
M|Reve|tx|**rv** — Total money earned from selling pd/services before expenses. The "top line" of the income statement.
M|Reve|- **|** Every feature shd connect to rv (direct or indirect). If you can't articulate rv impact, prioritization becomes impossible.
M|Reve|- **|** Sum of all cs payments in a period
M|Reve|- **|** Growth rate matters more than absolute number (context-dependent by stage)
M|Reve|tx|**ARPU (Average rv Per us)** — Average rv generated per individual us.
M|Reve|- **|** Measures per-seat monetization effectiveness. ct for seat-based pricing md.
M|Reve|- **|** `Total rv / Total us`
M|Reve|- **|** Varies by md; track tn more than absolute value
M|Reve|- **|** $5-50/month typical; B2B: $50-500+/month
M|Reve|tx|**ARPA (Average rv Per Account)** — Average rv generated per cs account.
M|Reve|- **|** Measures account-level deal size. ct for account-based pricing md.
M|Reve|- **|** `MRR / Active Accounts`
M|Reve|- **|** SMB SaaS: $100-$1K/month; Mid-mk: $1K-$10K; Enterprise: $10K+
M|Reve|tx|**ARPA/ARPU al** — Using both metrics together to understand monetization.
M|Reve|- **|** Prevents packaging mistakes. hi ARPA + lo ARPU = undermonetized per seat. lo ARPA + hi ARPU = small deal sizes.
M|Reve|- **|** $10K ARPA w/ 100 seats = $100 ARPU (reasonable). $10K ARPA w/ 1,000 seats = $10 ARPU (leaving money on table).
M|Reve|tx|**ACV (Annual Contract Value)** — Annualized recurring rv per contract (excludes one-time fees).
M|Reve|- **|** Compares economics across different contract structures. Enables sales compensation ds and segment al.
M|Reve|- **|** `Annual Recurring rv per Contract` (don't include setup fees, professional services)
M|Reve|- **|** SMB: $5K-$25K; Mid-mk: $25K-$100K; Enterprise: $100K+
M|Reve|tx|**MRR/ARR (Monthly/Annual Recurring rv)** — Predictable recurring rv normalized to monthly or annual.
M|Reve|- **|** The heartbeat of subscription businesses. Valued at 5-10x+ multiples. Track cp (new, expansion, churn).
M|Reve|- **|** `MRR = Sum of all recurring subscription rv per month`; `ARR = MRR × 12`
M|Reve|- **|** Growth rate and qual matter; track new MRR, expansion MRR, churned MRR, contracted MRR
M|Reve|tx|**Gross vs. Net rv** — Gross rv before vs. net rv after discounts, refunds, credits.
M|Reve|- **|** Discounts and refunds can hide bad acquisition qual or pd problems.
M|Reve|- **|** `Net rv = Gross rv - Discounts - Refunds - Credits`
M|Reve|- **|** Refunds >10% is a red flag; track by acquisition channel
M|Reve|tx|---
M|Rete|tx|Metrics that measure how well you keep and grow existing cs.
M|Rete|tx|**Churn Rate** — Percentage of cs who cancel in a period.
M|Rete|- **|** Silent killer of SaaS. Undermines all acquisition efforts. 5% monthly churn = 46% annual churn (compounding).
M|Rete|- **|** `cs Lost in Period / Starting cs`
M|Rete|- **|** <2% great, 2-5% acceptable, >5% crisis
M|Rete|- **|** <10% great, 10-30% acceptable, >30% crisis
M|Rete|- **|** Logo churn (cs count) differs from rv churn (dollar amount)
M|Rete|tx|**NRR (Net rv Retention)** — rv retention from existing cs inc expansion and contraction.
M|Rete|- **|** The holy grail metric. NRR >100% means you grow w/o new logos. Highly valued by investors.
M|Rete|- **|** `(Starting ARR + Expansion - Churn - Contraction) / Starting ARR × 100`
M|Rete|- **|** >120% excellent, 100-120% good, 90-100% acceptable, <90% problem
M|Rete|- **|** Start w/ $1M ARR, add $300K expansion, lose $100K to churn = $1.2M / $1M = 120% NRR
M|Rete|tx|**Expansion rv** — Additional rv from existing cs (upsells, cross-sells, usage growth).
M|Rete|- **|** Most capital-efficient rv (no CAC). shd drive NRR >100%.
M|Rete|- **|** `Sum of upsells + cross-sells + usage increases from existing cs`
M|Rete|- **|** shd represent 20-30% of total rv; drives NRR >100%
M|Rete|tx|**Quick Ratio (SaaS)** — rv gains vs. rv losses.
M|Rete|- **|** Shows if you're building on solid ground or running on a treadmill.
M|Rete|- **|** `(New MRR + Expansion MRR) / (Churned MRR + Contraction MRR)`
M|Rete|- **|** >4 excellent, 2-4 healthy, <2 leaky bucket
M|Rete|tx|---
M|Anal|tx|**rv Mix al** — Breakdown of rv by pd, segment, or channel.
M|Anal|- **|** Identifies which pd fund the business and where to invest. Reveals concentration risk.
M|Anal|- **|** `pd/Segment rv / Total rv × 100`
M|Anal|- **|** No single pd >60% ideal; diversification reduces risk
M|Anal|tx|**Cohort al** — Group cs by join date and track behavior over time.
M|Anal|- **|** Blended metrics hide ct tn. Shows whether business is improving or degrading.
M|Anal|- **|** Track retention, expansion, and LTV by cohort (e.g., "Jan 2024 cohort")
M|Anal|- **|** Recent cohorts shd perform same or better than old cohorts
M|Anal|tx|---
M|Anti|- **|** rv is top-line, not bottom-line. hi rv w/ negative margins is a disaster.
M|Anti|- **|** Total rv growth means nothing if driven by unsustainable discounting or margin-destroying deals.
M|Anti|- **|** ARPU that averages $10 SMB and $1,000 enterprise cs hides segment economics.
M|Anti|- **|** Churn rate alone doesn't tell the story—need to see cohort tn and NRR.
M|Anti|tx|---
M|When|**Us|**
M|When|it|Evaluating overall business health and pd-mk fit
M|When|it|Comparing perf across time periods or cohorts
M|When|it|Prioritizing features w/ direct monetization paths (ARPU impact, expansion enablers)
M|When|it|Communicating w/ leadership, board, or investors
M|When|it|Assessing retention problems (churn al, cohort degradation)
M|When|it|Measuring pricing or packaging changes (ARPU/ARPA shifts)
M|When|**Do|**
M|When|it|Evaluating profitability (use margin metrics instead)
M|When|- As|CAC, payback period)
M|When|it|Making pd investment decisions w/o cost context (rv alone isn't ROI)
M|When|it|Comparing across wildly different business md w/o normalization
M|When|tx|---
M|Step|tx|Use the templates in `template.md` to calculate your core rv metrics.
M|rv|tx|```
M|rv|tx|rv = Sum of all cs payments in period
M|rv|tx|```
M|rv|**Ex|**
M|rv|- Mo|$100,000
M|rv|it|rv = $100,000
M|rv|**Qu|**
M|rv|it|Is this gross or net rv? (Clarify if discounts/refunds are included)
M|rv|it|Is rv growing cohort-over-cohort, or just from new cs adds?
M|rv|it|What's the rv growth rate vs. headcount/cost growth rate?
M|rv|tx|---
M|ARPU|tx|```
M|ARPU|tx|ARPU = Total rv / Total us
M|ARPU|tx|```
M|ARPU|**Ex|**
M|ARPU|- To|$100,000/month
M|ARPU|- To|2,000
M|ARPU|it|ARPU = $100,000 / 2,000 = $50/us/month
M|ARPU|**Qu|**
M|ARPU|it|Is ARPU growing or shrinking over time?
M|ARPU|it|Is ARPU growth from price increases or mix shift (losing small cs)?
M|ARPU|it|How does ARPU vary by cohort? (Are new cs less valuable?)
M|ARPU|tx|---
M|ARPA|tx|```
M|ARPA|tx|ARPA = MRR / Active Accounts
M|ARPA|tx|```
M|ARPA|**Ex|**
M|ARPA|- MR|$100,000
M|ARPA|- Ac|200
M|ARPA|it|ARPA = $100,000 / 200 = $500/account/month
M|ARPA|**Qu|**
M|ARPA|it|Is ARPA growing from expansion or just larger new deals?
M|ARPA|it|How does ARPA compare across cs segments?
M|ARPA|it|Is ARPA hi but ARPU lo? (Undermonetized per seat)
M|ARPA|tx|---
M|ARPA|tx|```
M|ARPA|tx|ARPA = MRR / Active Accounts
M|ARPA|tx|ARPU = MRR / Total us
M|ARPA|tx|Average Seats per Account = ARPA / ARPU
M|ARPA|tx|```
M|ARPA|**Ex|**
M|ARPA|- AR|$500/month
M|ARPA|- AR|$50/month
M|ARPA|- Av|$500 / $50 = 10 seats/account
M|ARPA|**Qu|**
M|ARPA|it|Are you monetizing per seat effectively?
M|ARPA|it|cld you charge more per seat (raise ARPU)?
M|ARPA|it|cld you expand seat count per account (raise ARPA)?
M|ARPA|tx|---
M|ACV |tx|```
M|ACV |tx|ACV = Annual Recurring rv per Contract
M|ACV |tx|(Exclude one-time fees like setup, professional services)
M|ACV |tx|```
M|ACV |**Ex|**
M|ACV |it|cs signs 3-year contract for $300K total
M|ACV |it|ACV = $300K / 3 years = $100K/year
M|ACV |**Qu|**
M|ACV |it|How does ACV vary by segment (SMB vs. Enterprise)?
M|ACV |it|Is ACV growing over time (moving upmarket)?
M|ACV |it|Does ACV justify sales team cost structure?
M|ACV |tx|---
M|MRR/|tx|```
M|MRR/|tx|MRR = Sum of all recurring monthly subscriptions
M|MRR/|tx|ARR = MRR × 12
M|MRR/|Trac|
M|MRR/|it|New MRR (from new cs)
M|MRR/|it|Expansion MRR (from upsells/cross-sells)
M|MRR/|it|Churned MRR (from lost cs)
M|MRR/|it|Contraction MRR (from downgrades)
M|MRR/|tx|```
M|MRR/|**Ex|**
M|MRR/|- St|$500K
M|MRR/|- Ne|+$50K
M|MRR/|- Ex|+$20K
M|MRR/|- Ch|-$15K
M|MRR/|- Co|-$5K
M|MRR/|- En|$550K
M|MRR/|it|ARR = $550K × 12 = $6.6M
M|MRR/|**Qu|**
M|MRR/|it|Is MRR growth from new cs or expansion?
M|MRR/|it|Is churn/contraction increasing as you grow?
M|MRR/|- Wh|expansion:churn MRR? (Best: expansion > new)
M|MRR/|tx|---
M|Gros|tx|```
M|Gros|tx|Net rv = Gross rv - Discounts - Refunds - Credits
M|Gros|tx|```
M|Gros|**Ex|**
M|Gros|- Gr|$100K
M|Gros|- Di|-$10K
M|Gros|- Re|-$2K
M|Gros|- Ne|$88K
M|Gros|**Qu|**
M|Gros|it|Are discounts >20%? (Pricing power problem)
M|Gros|it|Are refunds >10%? (pd qual problem)
M|Gros|it|Do certain channels have higher discount/refund rates?
M|Gros|tx|---
M|Chur|tx|```
M|Chur|tx|Logo Churn Rate = cs Lost / Starting cs × 100
M|Chur|tx|rv Churn Rate = MRR Lost / Starting MRR × 100
M|Chur|tx|```
M|Chur|**Ex|**
M|Chur|- St|1,000
M|Chur|- Cu|30
M|Chur|it|Logo Churn = 30 / 1,000 = 3% monthly
M|Chur|**Ex|**
M|Chur|- St|$500K
M|Chur|- MR|$15K
M|Chur|it|rv Churn = $15K / $500K = 3% monthly
M|Chur|**Qu|**
M|Chur|it|Is churn rate accelerating or decelerating over time?
M|Chur|it|Are newer cohorts churning faster than older ones? (PMF degradation)
M|Chur|it|Is rv churn higher than logo churn? (Losing big cs)
M|Chur|**Co|**
M|Chur|- Mo|3% monthly ≠ 36% annual
M|Chur|- Fo|`Annual Churn = 1 - (1 - Monthly Churn)^12`
M|Chur|it|3% monthly = ~31% annual churn
M|Chur|tx|---
M|NRR |tx|```
M|NRR |tx|NRR = (Starting ARR + Expansion - Churn - Contraction) / Starting ARR × 100
M|NRR |tx|```
M|NRR |**Ex|**
M|NRR |- St|$5M
M|NRR |- Ex|+$800K
M|NRR |- Ch|-$300K
M|NRR |- Co|-$100K
M|NRR |- En|$5.4M
M|NRR |it|NRR = $5.4M / $5M = 108%
M|NRR |**Qu|**
M|NRR |it|Is NRR >100%? (You grow w/o new logos)
M|NRR |it|Is NRR improving or degrading cohort-over-cohort?
M|NRR |it|What's driving NRR? (Expansion or lo churn?)
M|NRR |tx|---
M|Expa|tx|```
M|Expa|tx|Expansion rv = Upsells + Cross-sells + Usage Growth (from existing cs)
M|Expa|tx|```
M|Expa|**Ex|**
M|Expa|- Up|$50K/month
M|Expa|- Cr|$20K/month
M|Expa|- Us|$10K/month
M|Expa|- To|$80K/month
M|Expa|**Qu|**
M|Expa|it|Is expansion rv growing as % of total rv?
M|Expa|it|What % of cs expand each year? (Expansion rate)
M|Expa|it|Are certain cohorts/segments more likely to expand?
M|Expa|tx|---
M|Quic|tx|```
M|Quic|tx|Quick Ratio = (New MRR + Expansion MRR) / (Churned MRR + Contraction MRR)
M|Quic|tx|```
M|Quic|**Ex|**
M|Quic|- Ne|$50K
M|Quic|- Ex|$20K
M|Quic|- Ch|$15K
M|Quic|- Co|$5K
M|Quic|it|Quick Ratio = ($50K + $20K) / ($15K + $5K) = $70K / $20K = 3.5
M|Quic|**Qu|**
M|Quic|it|Quick Ratio >4 = excellent (gains far exceed losses)
M|Quic|it|Quick Ratio 2-4 = healthy (sustainable growth)
M|Quic|it|Quick Ratio <2 = leaky bucket (fix retention before scaling)
M|Quic|tx|---
M|Reve|tx|```
M|Reve|tx|pd/Segment % = pd/Segment rv / Total rv × 100
M|Reve|tx|```
M|Reve|**Ex|**
M|Reve|- Pr|$300K
M|Reve|- Pr|$500K
M|Reve|- Pr|$200K
M|Reve|- To|$1M
M|Reve|- Pr|30%, pd B: 50%, pd C: 20%
M|Reve|**Qu|**
M|Reve|- Is|over-reliance on one pd)
M|Reve|it|Which pd are growing/shrinking?
M|Reve|it|Does rv mix match your st priorities?
M|Reve|tx|---
M|Coho|tx|Group cs by when they joined and track metrics over time.
