M|Exam|**Co|** SMB mk automation SaaS
M|Exam|**Re|**
M|Exam|- MR|$500K (growing 15% month-over-month)
M|Exam|- AR|$6M
M|Exam|- AR|$250/month (2,000 accounts)
M|Exam|- AR|$50/month (10,000 us)
M|Exam|**Re|**
M|Exam|- Mo|6% (increasing from 4% six months ago)
M|Exam|- Re|7% (losing larger cs)
M|Exam|- NR|85% (contracting)
M|Exam|- Ex|$5K/month (1% of MRR)
M|Exam|- Qu|1.2
M|Exam|**Co|**
M|Exam|tx|\| Cohort \| Month 6 Retention \|
M|Exam|tx|\|--------\|-------------------\|
M|Exam|tx|\| 6 months ago \| 75% \|
M|Exam|tx|\| 3 months ago \| 65% \|
M|Exam|tx|\| Current \| 58% \|
M|Exam|al|**
M|Exam|it|⚠️ hi churn (6% monthly = ~50% annual)
M|Exam|it|🚨 rv churn > logo churn (losing bigger cs)
M|Exam|it|🚨 NRR <100% (contracting, not expanding)
M|Exam|it|🚨 Cohort degradation (newer cs churn faster)
M|Exam|it|🚨 Quick Ratio 1.2 (leaky bucket)
M|Exam|**Ac|** STOP scaling acquisition. Fix retention first. Investigate:
M|Exam|it|Why are newer cohorts churning faster?
M|Exam|it|Why is expansion rv only 1% of MRR?
M|Exam|it|What's causing cs contraction?
M|Exam|tx|---
M|Exam|**Co|** Multi-pd SaaS platform
M|Exam|**Bl|**
M|Exam|- MR|$3M (growing 20% MoM)
M|Exam|- Bl|3%
M|Exam|- Bl|110%
M|Exam|**Bu|**
M|Exam|tx|\| pd \| rv \| % of Total \| Growth \| Churn \| NRR \|
M|Exam|tx|\|---------\|---------\|------------\|--------\|-------\|-----\|
M|Exam|tx|\| Legacy pd \| $2M \| 67% \| -5% MoM \| 8% \| 75% \|
M|Exam|tx|\| New pd \| $1M \| 33% \| +80% MoM \| 1% \| 150% \|
M|Exam|al|**
M|Exam|- 🚨|-5% growth, 8% churn, 75% NRR
M|Exam|- ✅ |+80% growth, 1% churn, 150% NRR
M|Exam|it|⚠️ Blended metrics hide the fact that 2/3 of rv is contracting
M|Exam|it|⚠️ hi dependency on one pd (67% concentration risk)
M|Exam|**Ac|** Accelerate migration from legacy to new pd. Plan for legacy pd sunset.
M|Exam|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We grew rv 50% this year, we're crushing it!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** rv is the top line, not bottom line. You might be growing at a loss, destroying margins, or scaling unprofitable pd.
M|Pitf|fix|** Always pair rv metrics w/ margin metrics (see `saas-economics-efficiency-metrics`). $1M rv at 80% margin >> $2M rv at 20% margin.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "ARPU increased 30%!" (but cs count dropped 40%)
M|Pitf|**Co|** ARPU rose bc you lost all your small cs, not bc you improved monetization.
M|Pitf|fix|** al ARPU by cohort and segment. True ARPU improvement = same cs paying more, not losing cheap cs.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Blended churn is stable at 3%"
M|Pitf|**Co|** Blended metrics can hide that new cohorts churn at 6% while old cohorts churn at 1%. pd-mk fit is degrading.
M|Pitf|fix|** Always al retention by cohort. If newer cohorts perform worse, stop scaling and fix the pd.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Logo churn is only 2%, we're great!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** You might be losing 2% of cs but 10% of rv if you're churning large cs.
M|Pitf|fix|** Track both logo churn AND rv churn. If rv churn > logo churn, you're losing hi-value cs.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We lost 50 cs this month" (no context on who)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Losing 50 small cs ($10/month) is different from losing 50 enterprise cs ($10K/month).
M|Pitf|fix|** Segment churn al by cs size, cohort, and reason. Weight by rv impact, not just logo count.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "3% monthly churn is fine, that's only 36% annually"
M|Pitf|**Co|** Churn compounds. 3% monthly = 31% annual churn, not 36%. Math: `1 - (1 - 0.03)^12 = 31%`.
M|Pitf|fix|** Use the correct formula when converting monthly to annual churn. Don't just multiply by 12.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Gross rv is up 20%!" (but discounts/refunds doubled)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Net rv might be flat or shrinking. Discounts hide pricing power problems; refunds hide pd qual issues.
M|Pitf|fix|** Always track gross AND net rv. If discounts >20% or refunds >10%, investigate why.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "NRR is 105%, we're expanding!"
M|Pitf|**Co|** NRR can be >100% just from very lo churn, w/o meaningful expansion. True expansion-driven NRR is >120%.
M|Pitf|fix|** Break down NRR into cp: expansion MRR vs. churned/contracted MRR. Aim for expansion-driven NRR, not just lo churn.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "We're at $10M ARR!" (but $5M is from one cs)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Losing that one cs cuts rv in half. Roadmap becomes hostage to one cs's requests.
M|Pitf|fix|** Track rv concentration. Ideal: Top cs <10% of rv, Top 10 cs <40%. Diversify early.
M|Pitf|tx|---
M|Pitf|**Sy|** "Our ARPU is $100" (average of $10 SMB and $1,000 enterprise)
M|Pitf|**Co|** Blended ARPU hides segment economics. Can't make smart acquisition or pd decisions.
M|Pitf|fix|** Calculate ARPU/ARPA by segment (SMB, mid-mk, enterprise). op each segment independently.
M|Pitf|tx|---
